The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for finding maximum cliques, which are topics covered in the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Graph Theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the intersection number of graphs, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and the label representation of graphs, which is a topic in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
